{"questionId":"21096","questionHtml":"<p>If the observer stands directly under point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math> for one minute, point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> will pass over his&nbsp;head <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> times.</p>\n<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>appropriate working towards finding the period&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>period</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6666</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>rotations per minute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mtext>their&nbsp;period</mtext></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp;(must be an integer) (accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21096","referenceCode":"21M.2.SL.TZ2.7e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"If the observ